A vintage-style illustration of a scientist's workbench featuring a brass microscope examining a small clockwork mechanism, while nearby a separate identical mechanism sits in a simple glass jar labeled only with a checkmark symbol. The scene shows warm amber lighting from an oil lamp casting soft shadows across scattered engineering blueprints and precision measuring tools. The aesthetic evokes 1920s scientific illustration with muted sepia tones, crosshatching textures, and aged paper quality. Delicate gears and springs are visible inside both mechanisms, suggesting the concept of isolating and testing individual components outside their complex housing. A magnifying loupe rests beside a small toolkit with tiny screwdrivers arranged neatly.
